and in doing so apply the standards and codes of good practice as stated in Chapter 4 of ‘het Stooktoestellenbesluit’.</li><li><strong>every 5 years</strong>, follow a refresher training at a recognised training centre. Download the overview list of recognised training centres for:<ul><li><a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.opleidingscentra_technici_gasvormige_brandstof.pdf\">gaseous fuel technicians</a>, <a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.opleidingscentra_technici_vloeibare_brandstof.pdf\">liquid fuel technicians</a> or <a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.opleidingscentra_technici_verwarmingsaudit.pdf\">heating audit technicians</a>. </li><li>The latest date for following a refresher training can be found:<ul><li>on your certificate of competence</li><li>or in the overview lists of <a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.technici_gasvormige_brandstof.pdf\">gaseous fuel technicians</a>, <a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.technici_vloeibare_brandstof.pdf\">liquid fuel technicians</a> or <a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.technici_verwarmingsaudit.pdf\">heating audit technicians</a>. </li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>correctly and fully complete reports</strong>, sign them and retain them for at least 1 year</li><li>hold <strong>insurance </strong>for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li><strong>report every change of identification</strong> data (such as address, e-mail address) immediately via <a href=\"mailto:erkenningen.omgeving@vlaanderen.be\">erkenningen.omgeving@vlaanderen.be</a></li><li>pay the<a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\"> annual fee</a> for the supervision of the recognition. The first payment is to be made in the year following the year in which you obtained the Flemish recognition certificate. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is still not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse. </li></ul><p><a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-erkende-technici-centrale-verwarming\">More info on the obligations</a> for recognised technicians can be found on the Department of Environment and Spatial Development website.</p><p> </p>","en-x-generated":"<p>To be approved as a liquid fuel technician, gaseous fuel technician or heating audit technician, you must meet:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all environmental recognitions<ul><li>in the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not been convicted in a <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">Member State of the European Economic Area</a> for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special recognition condition</strong>:<ul><li>be a natural person,</li><li>be in possession of a <strong>certificate of competence</strong> for liquid fuel, gaseous fuel or heating audit. The certificate must have been issued by a recognised training centre. </li></ul></li></ul><p>More info can be found in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woI