n for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li>special conditions of recognition:<ul><li>be a natural person</li><li>be in possession of a <strong>certificate of competence in refrigeration technology of category I, II, III or IV ('European certificate')</strong>.</li></ul></li></ul><h3>You already have a European certificate as a refrigeration technician</h3><p>If you already have a <strong>European certificate</strong> as a refrigeration technician, you can also obtain the Flemish recognition certificate. However, you must register with the Flemish government before you start working in the Flemish Region. This obligation applies to technicians who:</p><ul><li>obtained a European certificate outside the Flemish Region</li><li>have obtained a European certificate in the Flemish Region, but do not yet have a Flemish recognition certificate.</li></ul><p>If the European certificate is older than five years at the time of registration, the refrigeration technician must first pass the <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-koeltechnicus\">update exam at an accredited training centre</a> in order to obtain Flemish accreditation. </p><h2>Period of validity and obligations</h2><p>Recognition is valid for <strong>an indefinite</strong> period. However, as a recognised technician, you must fulfil some obligations.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-koeltechnicus\">More info on the obligations for accredited refrigeration technicians</a>.</p><p>The <strong>company </strong>for which the technician works must also have an <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-een-koeltechnisch-bedrijf\">accreditation as a refrigeration technician</a>.</p>","nl":"<p>Om erkend te worden als <strong>koeltechnicus </strong>moet u voldoen aan:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.e